\begin_layout Paragraph
Methodology
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Growth model with (1) technology (aggregate production function and capital
 accumulation equation) and (2) utility function for the stand-in household
 that depends on the paths of consumption and leisure and three types of
 taxes (consumption, labor income, and capital income)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Key Element
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Differences in output per capita can be accounted by: (1) exogenous level
 of technology, (2) capital factor, (3) labor factor, and (4) productivity.
 
