\begin_layout Paragraph
Main Results
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(1) and (2) are assumed same across countries; (3) accounts for France due
 to its higher intratemporal (consumption-leisure) tax wedge; and (4) accounts
 for Japan, which is poorer due to lower productivity (the most important
 factor according to the author)
