SAMPLE QUESTION:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Problem*
In their paper 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Putting Home Economics into Macroeconomics
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 (FRB-QR 1993), Greenwood, Rogerson, and Wright develop a model with home
 production.
 Briefly describe why they want to construct such a model and the key model
 feature that accomplished the task.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Solution*
The primary motivation for their paper is that investment in standard RBC
 model is too volatile while the consumption is too smooth.
 Furthermore, the significance of home production in economic activities
 has long been recognized, but its relevance for business cycle research
 has only been recently investigated.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Solution*
The authors introduce a home production function into the model and expand
 the household choices for allocating output.
 Specifically, the household now divides output between consumption, investment
 in business capital, and investment in household capital.
 Since home production allows more substitution into and out of market activity
 in response to shocks, investment is less volatile to the standard RBC
 model.
 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
