Persistence: next-period production depends on amount produced today + the
 shock next period, which is unobserved before making production decisions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Co-movement across commodities: multiple inputs are used to produce each
 single output, and outputs from previous periods are used as inputs to
 produce outputs next period.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Main Results
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The model can explain persistence and co-movement in consumption plans character
istic of typical business cycles.
