\begin_layout Solution*
The paper seeks to develop a model that explains two stylized facts; (1)
 stock of household capital is greater than the stock of business capital,
 and (2) investment in household capital is highly procyclical, leading
 business investment.
 To do so, they develop a Beckerian model of household production that treats
 business and household sectors almost symmetrically, where the only source
 of asymmetry between the two sectros is that capital can be produced in
 the market sector only.
 The model succeeds in explaining fact (1), but it cannot explain (2) even
 after adding increasing complementarity or adding capital adjustment costs.
 
